rts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + resilience_undermines_deterrence + time_of_perils_exit + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence → 14 time_of_perils_exit → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJy1WWtT20gW%2FSu3qJ1dm8HG8tuwTBUJMJNaklBANjUVUkpbats9SGptt4RxMslv39MtyZZBVJSh5gslpO5zz33fbn%2FZ8fmMpUHyUvp852Bnf5%2BOjo7oWjERUSLJU%2BzzCg%2FLiG7Sbsfp01KqwL8TfElLx%2B26A3fojtyx6ziu03edoeuMqKETGZMzahqsmwiYx1qnYZwIGZG3APQBdShmSnoLwQKD7Ey65NCMKZct2cpdpCGLdPGhSywSIQu0q2XIlwuWFF8GNEuTVPF8gxuyJOHKXYpk4fpCezKNEhHNi%2BVDimT5vbu1u1g1WovL4ZgbyLXIMel0NuPKbpdeqrm%2FVsAhxbUIBI887qaRz1UoIq5dnwNGmbfrpX1KRMhdOXNjYEEWvxdrGc6QAnFnJIjI1SJMA2ZtV3weETZpGbkMTDyrifGINfUp8xbENvYWmhhdrJIFnmci4ATHbj7rfUqMPZnv6z2wRzQYxiSVBVO8BTex0PAXGu%2BTBc88%2BC8N00eexTgkT4ax1MbS6wXYawwA6yQLoS2aTljks0BGnEKEW9CmT%2BtoOr37ZKia7fw%2BhlLYeMeClJOcWYRN4LUt2AuuE5qmK7J2Nhs1Lyt2QFcLJcKY3vMAccXpQsk%2FgJvt%2FvX0zenl8fXpCU1XNOcRVyzh7XhVRDn34Y2ymXbxcQ%2Fhk2RkjCWBZLHewa8qMSqHUiGc1xbT2drMHCyOERi6TVersB3IeSQVYqzxJR7sUTwZfG1aLO