cides) · 30%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + resilience_undermines_deterrence + space_expansion_backfires + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence → 15 space_expansion_backfires → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJy1WWtT20gW%2FSu3qJ1dm8FGsvELlqkiAWZSSzIUkJ2aCimnLbWtHmS1tlvCOJnkt%2B%2Fp1sMyNoUy1HyhhNR97rnv2%2B0vOz6fsjRMXkuf7xzu7O%2FT8fEx3SgmIkokeYp9XuJhEdFt2nHcA1pIFfr3gi9o4Y474964Px6Mh2PXHbu9sdsfuwNq6ETG5A6aBus2AuaJ1uk8ToSMyAsAfUgOxUxJLxAsNMjuqEMuTZkaswVbjoN0ziJdfOgQi8SchXqs5ZwvApYUX3o0TZNU8XzDeM6ShKvxQiTB2Bfak2mUiGhWLO9TJKvvx2u7i1WDUlwOx8ahLEUOSafTKVd2u%2FRSzf1SAZcU1yIUPPL4OI18ruYi4nrsc8Ao87Zc2iMdM6ziDzFEwzDjCfPupgIA5Zo%2BheLeyBHRWIt5GjJrweLzgGKuNHYy8PGsPsYv1uBnzAuIrawuNDG6XCYBnqci5AT3rj7rfUqMVZnv6z3ogJgwvEkqC6Z4C85ic6OF0HifBDzz4780HBB5FuOIPDmPpTb2LhdgrzEDbJQEQls0nbDIZ6GMOM0RdGGbPpUxdXb%2FyVA122EYKIWN9yxMOcmpRViFX9uCveI6oUm6JGtts1HzqmKHdB0oMY%2FpNx4iujhdKvkHcLPdP5%2B9O7s6uTk7pcmSZjziiiW8HS%2BLWOe%2BSNbMtIuPewiiJCNjLAk