trokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="16" y="1434" width="395" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+7+8+11+16]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   66k lives-eq/$1k · 68% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 30%&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + resilience_undermines_deterrence + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 animals_matter_a_lot → 8 suffering_focused → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence → 16 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWWtv2zgW%2FSsXwc6u3bUdyW8nmwHSxpkpNukESbrFoClcWqJtbiVRS0px3E7nt%2B8hJdly7aDq%2BEugSOS55z55L%2F3lyOczlgbJK%2Bnzo5Oj42M6Ozuje8VERIkkT7HPKzwsI3pI247bpaVUgf8o%2BJKW7qQ96U36k8FkOHHdidunmk5kTG6%2FblAeIqCda52GcSJkRN4CoCfkUMyU9BaCBQbTHbXJpRlTE7Zkq8kiDVmkiw9tYpEIWaAnWoZ8uWBJ8aVHszRJFc83TEKWJFxNliJZTHyhPZlGiYjmxfI%2BRbL8frK1u1g1WIvL4dgkkGuRQ9LpbMaV3S69VHN%2FrYBLimsRCB55fJJGPlehiLie%2BBwwyrxdL%2B1TIB4NhogmWoRpwIx1rLHGzFsQ21hMaGJ0s0oWeJ6JgBOcsvmsjykxFmG%2BrxuQD08amSSVBVO8CUOz0DAQGu%2BTBc988A8N40WexTglT4ax1MZW6wXYa1SAfslCaIumExb5LJARpxChErTo4zoSxo8fDVWznT%2FF3Euw8ZEFKSc5swiboGlZsJdcJzRNV2QtZTZqXlbshO4WSoQxveMBIoPTjZL%2FBW62%2B5fxm%2FHt%2Bf34gqYrmvOIK5bwVrwqIpT7Itky0wt8bCAAkoyMsSSQLNZb